A Security guard was killed yesterday at a hotel in Ikorodu, Lagos, while guests including three officials of the Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board (JAMB) were robbed. The incident occurred around 2:30am at Mabila Hotel. It was gathered that the armed men stormed the hotel while lodgers were asleep and broke into rooms. The gateman was said to have been shot while attempting to stop the robbers from fleeing. He was rushed to hospital where he died, The Nation learnt.   Bandits kill six soldiers in Taraba     Oil theft: Navy arrests 117 suspects, six vessels     Woman seeks justice after husband dies in police custody   It was gathered that one Prof. Odunsi was robbed of mobile phones, laptop and N20,000. Police spokesman Benjamin Hundeyin said the three JAMB officials were rescued. He said: “One Prof. Odunsi, an official of JAMB, who lodged at the hotel was robbed of his two Tecno phones, one HP Laptop and N20,000 cash. Similarly, two female officials of JAMB, who lodged at the hotel, were robbed of their phones and jewelry. “Police received a complaint that armed hoodlums gained entry into the hotel and deployment was made immediately. When the hoodlums sighted the police patrol van, they fled in a Lexus SUV. The gateman of the hotel, one Peter, 40, was shot while trying to prevent the armed men from escaping. “The Commissioner of Police, Abiodun Alabi, has ordered a manhunt for the culprits,” he said.